items.title: San Stae - Saint Stae
items.description:
Roberto Marinoni posted a photo:

La chiesa di San Stae (versione dialettale del nome Eustachio) esisteva a Venezia già nel 1127: divenuta fatiscente, a partire dal 1678 venne ricostruita in forme barocche.
L'interno è molto luminoso anche per via del colore bianco delle pareti.
Al centro della chiesa si trova la tomba del Doge Alvise Mocenigo, grazie al cui lascito testamentario fu possibile rifare la facciata agli inizi del Settecento.

----------

The church of San Stae (dialect version of the name Eustachio) existed in Venice as early as 1127: having become dilapidated, starting from 1678 it was rebuilt in baroque style. The interior is very bright also due to the white color of the walls. At the center of the church is the tomb of Doge Alvise Mocenigo, thanks to whose bequest it was possible to redo the façade at the beginning of the eighteenth century.

items.title: Porta della Carta ( 1442 )
items.description:
Caffe_Paradiso posted a photo:

Great ceremonial doorway into the palace, by Giovanni and Bartolomeo Buon, completed around 1442, connecting the newly constructed wing of the Palace with the south wall of St Marks Basilica. It includes a sculpture of the Doge Francesco Foscari kneeling before the lion of St Mark. Originally the whole gateway was painted and gilded.
